<%#
  Captain expectations / agreement. Displayed both on the invite modal
  (superadmin → add captain) and on the captain's own hub page so the
  terms are always one click away. Locals:
    hub_name (string)
%>
<div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
  <p>
    Thanks for stepping up to captain
    <strong><%= hub_name %></strong>. Here's what you're signing up for —
    and what's still up to us.
  </p>

  <div>
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 font-bold mb-1">What you'll do</div>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
      <li>Keep listings accurate — edit any mic in your hub, approve community suggestions, set statuses.</li>
      <li>Run the queue: approve or reject submissions, claims, and challenges promptly (aim for within a few days).</li>
      <li>Be a fair broker. Don't favor your own mics or shut out competitors. Decisions should be defensible to anyone.</li>
      <li>Loop us in on edge cases — disputes, abuse, anything that needs a human call from CocoScout.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div>
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 font-bold mb-1">What's not yours to decide</div>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
      <li>This role isn't permanent or exclusive. CocoScout retains the right to add additional captains, replace you, or remove the captain role entirely from this hub at any time.</li>
      <li>You can step down whenever — just let us know.</li>
      <li>City-level branding, hub copy, and policy stay with CocoScout.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
    Questions? Reply in CocoScout DMs or email
    <a href="mailto:hello@cocoscout.com" class="text-pink-600 hover:underline">hello@cocoscout.com</a>.
  </p>
</div>
